  "prompt": "What is the smartest thing you've seen an animal do?",
  "response": "There have been many remarkable examples of animal intelligence across different species. One particularly impressive instance involves crows, specifically the New Caledonian crow. These birds have demonstrated the ability to use tools in complex ways, such as using sticks to extract insects from tree bark. \n\nIn one study, researchers presented crows with a series of tasks that required multiple steps to obtain a food reward. The crows were able to plan ahead, showing foresight by selecting and using the right tools in the correct order. For example, they would use one tool to obtain a second tool and then use that second tool to get the food.\n\nAdditionally, dolphins have exhibited impressive communication skills and problem-solving abilities. In some cases, they have been observed coordinating complex hunting techniques and using unique vocalizations to work together effectively.\n\nThese examples highlight the incredible cognitive abilities found in the animal kingdom, demonstrating that intelligence takes many forms across different species.",
